9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 695, L.D. 1793, “An Act to Improve
10 Management and Reduce the Volume of Solid Waste”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'An Act to Amend Eligibility Criteria Under the Maine Solid Waste Diversion Grant
13 Program'
14 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
15 following:
16 'Sec. 1. 38 MRSA §2201-B, sub-§4, as enacted by PL 2015, c. 461, §7, is amended
17 to read:
18 4. Eligibility criteria. The department may disburse grants under the program to any
19 public or private entity demonstrating that a proposed program, project, initiative or activity
20 is, in the department's determination, likely to increase the diversion of solid waste from
21 disposal within a particular community, municipality or region or the State, including, but
22 not limited to, municipal or regional composting, organics recovery or recycling programs,
23 including the establishment of such programs or the purchase of infrastructure, equipment
24 or other items necessary to implement such programs or improve existing programs;
25 programs designed to provide equipment for or otherwise support residential composting
26 and recycling; programs or business models designed to collect, transport for processing or
27 process organic or recyclable materials; pilot programs designed to evaluate the feasibility
28 of targeted composting, organics recovery, recycling or other waste management programs
29 or initiatives; and initiatives or programs designed to educate certain categories of
30 individuals or the general public about composting, organics recovery or recycling or to
31 otherwise improve individual or community waste management practices; and programs,
32 projects, initiatives or activities relating to the collection and transportation of waste that is
33 diverted from disposal. Grants disbursed by the department under the program to public
34 and regional entities may cover necessary costs incidental to or associated with the
35 implementation of a proposed program, project, initiative or activity, including, but not
36 limited to, the hiring of or contracting with consultants or specialists, the conducting of
