5 SUMMARY
66 This amendment replaces the bill and changes the title. It amends eligibility criteria
77 for grants under the Maine Solid Waste Diversion Grant Program established in the Maine
88 Revised Statutes, Title 38, section 2201-B to authorize disbursement of grants to public
99 and regional entities to cover necessary costs incidental to or associated with the
1100 implementation of a proposed program, project, initiative or activity, including, but not
1111 limited to, the hiring of or contracting with consultants or specialists, the conducting of
1122 feasibility studies and the promotion of collaborative regional efforts relating to the
1133 collection and transportation of solid waste. It also expands grant eligibility to public or
1144 private entities for programs, projects, initiatives or activities relating to the collection and
1155 transportation of waste that is diverted from disposal.
